Ordered Three crunchy rolls, did not get that. When I called to report the mistake, they answered the crunchiness is inside the rolls, no, it wasn’t. The rolls were bland and dry. Asked for Low sodium soy sauce because I have heart issues, I got salty soy sauce and one small container for three rolls. They did manage to prepare my husband’s ribs the way I asked but barely enough to fill my husband up, $30.00 spent and we’re still hungry. The delivery was faster than the 1 hour and a half originally stated.  Will not be ordering from them again. Mind you, all the instructions were online and they still messed up with no offer to fix their mistakes, got nothing but excuses. You would think they would want to make sure every customer is satisfied considering there aren’t many but I guess they don’t need my money, then again with those prices they probably do not need to satisfy every customer. I’ll remember that when I think about donating again to the restaurant fund to keep them open.
